The paper discusses a technique for training neural networks and improving their architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of "surgery" to transfer trained weights from one network to another after changes in features and architecture. This technique is relevant to several sub-categories of arXiv CS, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, given the focus on neural networks and their architecture, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
